
<!-- html/index.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Apache in Docker</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Hello from Apache inside Docker!</h1>
</body>
</html>
# Use official Apache image
FROM httpd:2.4

# Copy custom HTML into Apache's web root
COPY html/ /usr/local/apache2/htdocs/
docker build -t apache-server .
docker run -dit --name apache-container -p 8080:80 apache-server
http://localhost:8080


6. (Optional) Live Editing with Volume Mount
Instead of copying files during build, mount the folder live:

bash
Copy code
docker run -dit --name apache-dev \
  -p 8080:80 \
  -v $(pwd)/html:/usr/local/apache2/htdocs/ \
  httpd:2.4
Now changes in html/ reflect instantly.

